We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Direct the Bids and Award Committee to submit the contracts and purchase order together with the supporting documents as required in COA Circular No. 2009-001;

Require the Municipal Planning and Development Officer to submit the Approved Program of Works with detailed engineering, Status of Work Accomplished validated by the LGU’s Inspectorate Committee;

Require the Municipal Engineer to submit the Inspection Report, pictures, Certificates of Completion and Acceptance, and other pertinent documents for every infrastructure project implemented by administration; and

Direct the Municipal Treasurer to ensure that all of the disbursement vouchers for the 20% Development Fund are properly labelled/stamped.

We recommended Local Chief Executive to:

Require the Municipal Social Welfare and Development Officer and the Municipal Treasurer to attach the following documents in their liquidation:

