Recommendations
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Direct the Bids and Awards Committee to:
Regulate the LGU’s government procurements to ensure the proper employment of competitive bidding unless an alternative mode of procurement is practicable following the provisions of the Revised IRR of RA 9184;
Ensure that the Annual Procurement Plan (APP) is properly prepared following the prescribed format by the GPPB indicating the proper mode of procurement and for any changes thereof, a BAC Resolution approved by the HoPe, shall be issued, and the APP shall be updated accordingly before pursuing another mode of procurement;
Furnish a copy of the Project Procurement Management Plan (PPMP) and Annual Investment Plan (AIP) to the Office of the Auditor to support the APP;
Strictly observe that no procurement shall be authorized and undertaken unless it is following the approved APP.
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that the disbursement vouchers are supported with required documents; and
Ensure adherence to the guidelines outlined in RA 9184 and its IRR throughout the procurement process of goods, services, and infrastructure projects to promote transparency, efficiency, and cost-effectiveness.

