We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to:

Create an inventory committee to conduct an actual physical inventory taking of all properties, plant and equipment headed by the General Services Officer and witnessed by any representative of the Commission on Audit;

Direct the General Service Officer to maintain stock cards of each property, plant and equipment bearing property number while the Municipal Accountant to maintain a subsidiary ledger card on each equipment account;

Direct the General Service Officer to identify unserviceable properties and prepare an Inspection and Inventory Report for disposal; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare necessary adjustments on the deficiencies noted in the course of inventory taking and make reconciliation with inventory report, stock cards and subsidiary ledgers.

We recommended the following courses of action which the Municipal Accountant has agreed to:

Review the transaction charged to Construction in Progress accounts and ensure that only accumulated cost of infrastructure assets, buildings or structures which are still in the process of contribution, development or acquisition be recorded thereof;

Make proper reclassification to the appropriate PPE accounts upon completion;

Reconcile with the records of the Office of the Municipal Engineer and disclose the details of Construction in Progress accounts in the notes to financial statements and subsidiary schedule; and

Make necessary adjusting or correcting entries and strictly observe the proper accounts prescribed in the Revised Chart of Accounts for Local Government Units for accurate and reliable presentation of the affected accounts in the financial statements.

