Management’s Comment:
The management recognized the recommendations and committed to implement the recommendations.

We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
Require the GSO to:
Maintain Property Cards (PC) for the PPEs to account for the receipt and disposition;
Ensure that the deliveries of properties and equipment are immediately recorded in the Property Cards (PC) based on the AIR and other supporting documents;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Maintain Ledger Cards for each category of PPEs to record deliveries;
Make reconciliation with inventory reports, property cards, and subsidiary ledgers;
Ensure that the deliveries of properties and equipment are immediately recorded in the PPE Subsidiary Ledger Cards based on the AIR and other supporting documents; and
Ensure strict adherence to the above-stated laws, rules, and regulations.
Management’s Comment:
The management will comply with the audit recommendations.

We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
Require all officials and employees concerned to prepare properly accomplished drivers trip tickets and pre-approved before undertaking the trip;
Direct the General Services Officer to submit Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption of government motor transportation; strictly comply with the provisions of the Manual on Audit of Fuel Consumption of Government Motor Vehicles as prescribed under COA Circular No. 77-61 to be properly guided in the documentation of fuel consumption and the use of government vehicles/equipment as well as to be able to regulate fuel consumption;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Make sure that payments for fuel expenses are duly supported with filled out drivers trip tickets for proper evaluation of the propriety and reasonableness of fuel consumption before recording the same in the books of accounts;
Execute the proper recording of transactions in the JEVs; transactions with two or more types of expenses should be recorded separately in their respective proper accounts;
Make any necessary adjusting entries to ensure that the financial accounts are presented fairly; and
Maintain a ledger for the fuel, oil and lubricants expense account to avoid errors in the presentation of the same.
Require the GSO to submit to the Commission on Audit, the Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption not later than ten (10) days of the succeeding month for validation.
Managements Comment:
The LGU has owned a fuel depot for use in the mobilization of the heavy equipment and other vehicles. They will require officials and employees to provide drivers trip tickets and the GSO to submit monthly report of fuel consumption.

