We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:

1. Direct the LDRRM Officer to submit Local Sanggunian Resolution and the declaration of the state of calamity for the utilization of QRF;
2. Direct the LDRRMO to prepare and submit the Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF using the prescribed format (Annex B of COA Circular No. 2012-002) on or before the 15th day after the end of each month through the LDRRMC and Local Development Council (LDC) to the Audit Team. The report shall be prepared and certified correct by the Municipal Accountant-Designate;
3. Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to maintain separate Registries of Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations (RAAOs) for the LDRRMF as required in Section 5.1.4 of COA Circular No. 2012-002.
4. Direct the Municipal Accountant-Designate to strictly comply with Sections 5.1.10 and 5.1.11of COA Circular No. 2012-002 on the treatment of unexpended LDRRMF, which shall be transferred to the Special Trust Fund under the account of Trust Liability-DRMM in the Trust Fund books.

We have recommended the Local Chief Executive must be compliant to the general guidelines, reporting and monitoring of the information and publicity on Programs/Projects/Activities (PPAs) as imposed in COA Circular No. 2013-004 dated January 31, 2013. In line with this, the management shall:

Submit to the Audit Team the list of all on-going government Programs/Projects/Activities (PPAs) and those that are to be implemented during the year;

Inform this office within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/ activity that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted;

And submit to this Office a Quarterly Report on the Publicized Government Projects/Programs/Activities.

