We have recommended to the management for executive action:

a. Creation of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board in accordance with the provision of law;

b.	The plan should be reviewed and updated as required by law to ensure its sustainability, relevance and effectiveness;

c. Campaigns should be collaborated with the barangay officials concerned; and

Continued and stricter implementation of waste segregation, and thorough collection of waste based on set schedules.

We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive to:
Create a team/committee to conduct an immediate physical count of all its property, plant and equipment. They are required to submit the RPCPPE on or before January 31 of each year, copy furnished the COA Auditor concerned pursuant to Section 124 of NGAS Manual, Volume I and Section 490 of GAAM, Volume I;

Further, the committee should be required to check the condition of the property. Any damage, obsolete and unserviceable property shall be reported in the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) and Waste Materials Report and immediately request for disposal. Lastly, the inventory reports should be reconciled with the accounting records to determine the correctness of the property records;
Require each Department Head to conduct every year a physical inventory count of all properties under their office and to submit inventory report to the inventory committee for the random validation of the existence of the property;
Require both the Accountant and General Services Office to maintain and update records and ledgers all properties owned by the Municipality; and
Direct Accountant to provide the correct depreciation expense on all Depreciable Assets to present the correct net book value in the financial statement.

